MedTwin AI – Blockchain Module Implementation Report

Project: MedTwin AI – Autonomous AI Healthcare Digital Twin

Module: Blockchain

Developer: Tanishka Chaudhary

Network: Polygon Amoy Testnet

Framework: Hardhat

Language: Solidity

Date: July 2026

1. Introduction

The blockchain module of MedTwin AI provides an immutable audit trail for medical documents. Instead of storing sensitive medical reports directly on the blockchain, the system stores a cryptographic hash of each document. This approach ensures data integrity, reduces blockchain storage costs, and protects patient privacy.

The blockchain layer has been developed independently inside the blockchain/ directory without modifying any other project modules.

2. Objective

The objective of this module is to:

Record the cryptographic hash of uploaded medical documents.
Associate the document with the doctor's blockchain wallet.
Record the timestamp when the document was registered.
Prevent duplicate document registrations.
Allow anyone to verify whether a document has already been recorded.
